Floats are evil.<p>Here&#x27;s a program:<p><pre><code>  int main(int argc, char* argv[]) {
    double x = 0.75;
    double t1 = 0.50000025;
    int i, j;
    int n8 = 93 * 100;
    for (i = 0;; i++) {
      for (j = 0; j<n8; j++)
        x = sqrt(exp(log(x) / t1));
      printf(&quot;%d %f
&quot;, i, x);
    }
  }
</code></pre>
Watch what happens to the performance as i passes 4632.<p>The full saga is here; AFAICT it&#x27;s a pathological edge case in glibc. <a href="https://plus.google.com/118274112180368285367/posts/ZPL5LTK9gpm" rel="nofollow">https://plus.google.com/118274112180368285367/posts/ZPL5LTK9...</a>
